cs.CL, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) techniques to translate process models into NL descriptions. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper addresses the issue of sharing process models and proposes a solution to improve the understandability and reproducibility of these models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses an encoder-decoder paradigm, which is a common technique in machine learning and NLP. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper proposes a novel approach for translating process models using an encoder-decoder model. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with extracting information from process models and generating NL descriptions.
